Here’s a Happy quokka to welcome the weekend with a smile via @cruzysuzy 😊

The quokka, also known as the short-tailed scrub wallaby, is a little macropod about the size of a domestic cat. A quokka weighs 2.5 to 5.0 kg (5.5 to 11 lb) and is 40 to 54 cm (16 to 21 in) long with a 25-to-30 cm-long (9.8-to-12 in) tail.

It was first described by Dutch mariner Samuel Volckertzoon when he wrote of sighting "a wild cat" on Rottnest Island in 1658.

In the wild, the quokka’s roaming is restricted to a very small range in the South West of Western Australia, with a number of small scattered populations. One large population exists on Rottnest Island and a smaller population is on Bald Island near Albany.

📷 @cruzysuzy #nature
📍Rottnest Island, Australia

Heat warnings have also been issued for Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Italy, Romania, Serbia and Turkey. Deadly wildfires have swept across parts of Turkey in recent days and forced the evacuation of tourist resorts.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on August 06, 2021. May be an image of child, sky, ocean and text that says 'Residents of the Greek capital, Athens have been warned to stay indoors with their windows closed because of poor air quality after a wildfire raged Tuesday in the suburbs.north of the capital. The extreme heat forced the Ministry of Culture to close the Acropolis and other ancient sites from noon to 5 p.m. local this week.'.

TURKEY IS ON FIRE! This needs to be brought to EVERYONE'S attention! Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 30, 2021. May be an image of sky and text that says 'More than 60 wildfires have broken out across 17 provinces on Turkey's Aegean and Mediterranean coasts this week, killing at least 4 people along with thousands of farm animals and sending 60 more people to the hospital as their homes burned down வ்கி்்ன் က် ជញ ചോടት'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 30, 2021. May be an image of fire, outdoors and text that says 'So far, 18 villages have been evacuated and 35 aircrafts, 457 vehicles and 4,000 personnel have been involved in the firefighting efforts, as separate wildfires raged in the provinces of Osmaniye, Kayseri, Kocaeii, Adana, Mersin and Kutahya.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 30, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'Turkey has battled a series of disasters caused by extreme weather conditions this summer, including flash floods last week that killed 6 people in the Black Sea region. These disasters have been devastating to the wildlife in Turkey, killing countless innocent animals and destroying their homes'.
